tspan.tspan: Sustained Attention Response Task (SART) performance results 20s prior to a probe.
standard deviation of reaction time (stdRT). The left panels show the mean performance of
each group (Controls in orange and ADHD in blue) across blocks (
= 4 blocks) with error bars representing the standard error of the
performance variables. The right panels show the overall mean and standard error by group. Stars denote the significance level of block effect
on performance (left panels) and performance differences between groups (right panels) as determined by linear mixed-effect models (ns:
< 0.001).When compared to whole-task performance analysis, group differences in commission
errors showed reduced significance (p < 0.05) and group differences in stdRT became non-significant. However, there was a significant group
by block interaction for stdRT, indicating that group differences in response variability varied across task blocks.
